{"type":"user.message","data":{"content":"I'm building a photo viewer page in my .NET MAUI app targeting .NET 10. I want\nthe image to fill the entire screen edge-to-edge, going behind the status bar\nand navigation bar. But my image still has padding around it even though I set\nSafeAreaEdges=\"None\" on the ContentPage. What am I missing?\n","transformedContent":"<current_datetime>2026-05-11T01:08:49.061Z</current_datetime>\n\nI'm building a photo viewer page in my .NET MAUI app targeting .NET 10. I want\nthe image to fill the entire screen edge-to-edge, going behind the status bar\nand navigation bar. But my image still has padding around it even though I set\nSafeAreaEdges=\"None\" on the ContentPage. What am I missing?","attachments":[],"interactionId":"bb729049-174f-4c6d-8664-3cd8f26c9648"},"id":"6f07922d-a8ae-4554-be01-dbcdf7c0401b","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:08:49.061Z","parentId":"af515fd1-443e-4d24-9d0f-09ca445c4dd6"}
